WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.080 --> 00:00:03.230
This is Career Ops. I forked an open source

2
00:00:03.140 --> 00:00:05.700
job search pipeline and rebuilt it into

3
00:00:05.550 --> 00:00:08.940
a cost-governed system run by 52 scheduled

4
00:00:08.920 --> 00:00:11.970
agents. It runs my actual job search.

5
00:00:12.260 --> 00:00:14.130
One honest note before we start.

6
00:00:14.300 --> 00:00:16.930
the real dashboard shows recruiter names

7
00:00:16.800 --> 00:00:19.350
and salary numbers. so what you're watching

8
00:00:19.260 --> 00:00:22.520
is the same system pointed at a demo dataset.

9
00:00:23.000 --> 00:00:26.190
Every company on this screen is invented.

10
00:00:26.120 --> 00:00:29.230
Everything else is real. This is the Apply

11
00:00:29.160 --> 00:00:32.930
Now board. Every role here ran through triage.

12
00:00:33.140 --> 00:00:35.150
a multimodal scoring council.

13
00:00:35.380 --> 00:00:38.110
and adjudication before it earned a rank.

14
00:00:38.580 --> 00:00:40.540
These scores aren't hardcoded.

15
00:00:40.710 --> 00:00:42.340
They're computed per role.

16
00:00:42.540 --> 00:00:45.430
grounded in my actual CV corpus.

17
00:00:45.320 --> 00:00:49.150
with the source cited. Over 1100 role reports

18
00:00:49.060 --> 00:00:50.790
have come through this pipeline.

19
00:00:51.060 --> 00:00:52.650
Here's the part that matters.

20
00:00:52.900 --> 00:00:55.570
I don't just run agents. I watch them.

21
00:00:55.760 --> 00:00:59.270
Batch telemetry with per run cost and timing.

22
00:00:59.449 --> 00:01:02.050
a regression guard that flags when something

23
00:01:02.020 --> 00:01:05.090
quietly breaks. a health agent that checks

24
00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:08.370
O auth tokens. quotas. and scheduled jobs

25
00:01:08.420 --> 00:01:10.930
every morning. When you operate agents in

26
00:01:10.860 --> 00:01:14.090
production. the hard part isn't generation.

27
00:01:14.180 --> 00:01:15.950
It's knowing when they're wrong.

28
00:01:16.180 --> 00:01:17.970
One story to make that concrete:

29
00:01:18.140 --> 00:01:22.010
a model vendor deprecated a single API parameter.

30
00:01:22.420 --> 00:01:25.210
Every batch started failing silently.

31
00:01:25.080 --> 00:01:28.030
and the queue just kept retrying forever.

32
00:01:27.940 --> 00:01:30.250
No crash. no error email.

33
00:01:30.420 --> 00:01:33.230
nothing. The dashboard is how I caught it.

34
00:01:33.400 --> 00:01:37.250
The batch panel showed 100% errors at zero

35
00:01:37.140 --> 00:01:39.990
progress. Symptom. telemetry.

36
00:01:39.940 --> 00:01:43.000
fix. That loop is the whole reason this

37
00:01:42.880 --> 00:01:46.250
page exists. I built this to run my own

38
00:01:46.160 --> 00:01:48.950
search. but the muscle is the one a forward

39
00:01:48.840 --> 00:01:51.970
deployed role needs. Stand up an agentic

40
00:01:51.880 --> 00:01:54.110
system against a real workflow.

41
00:01:54.240 --> 00:01:56.970
instrument it. and keep it honest.

42
00:01:56.880 --> 00:01:58.870
Even this voice is synthetic.

43
00:01:59.040 --> 00:02:01.610
cloned from me with my consent.

44
00:02:01.470 --> 00:02:03.240
The code is on my GitHub.

45
00:02:03.260 --> 00:02:06.890
and I write about what I learn at thestorytellermitch.com.

46
00:02:07.280 --> 00:02:08.370
Check the receipts.
